The paper deals with the Asymmetric Traveling Salesman Problem (ATSP) and focuses on negative results in the framework of the Sherali-Adams (SA) Lift and Project method. This involves studying the structure of digraphs and their fractional feasible solutions, which are topics that fall under the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
